{"label": "reporter-direct", "event": {"type": "agent.message", "text": "REPORTFMTOK\n\n**ADK sub_agents**\n\n**Summary:** A coordinator delegates work to specialized sub-agents by creating self-contained task instructions that include all necessary context, then synthesizes the results when the sub-agents complete their work.\n\n**Details:**\n- The coordinator uses `create_agent(agent_name, task)` to spawn a sub-agent with a single, self-contained task that includes all context, constraints, and data the sub-agent needs\u2014since sub-agents cannot see conversation history.\n- The coordinator monitors sub-agent progress with `list_agents()` and sends follow-up instructions via `send_to_agent()` for iterative work, allowing the sub-agent to refine or extend its output.\n- Once sub-agents finish and report results, the coordinator synthesizes findings into a response for the user rather than relaying raw sub-agent output verbatim.\n\nREPORTER-AGENT-OK\n\nHOUSESTYLEOK"}}
